manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Hllhunkhe Waterproof case for Samsung Galaxy A53 5G Main Features: Fully sealed and extremely waterproof, submersible up to 20ft/6m deep, Exceeded IP68 standard.Ultra-thin & lightweight: 2.0oz/56.7g. 0.5 inch/12.6 mm thickness.Easy to snap on and take off, special sound enhancement system provides the best call and audio quality.Tough but soft material on case frame is more durable compared to other plastic waterproof cases, but absorbs shock impact for a better protection.Multi-functional: This case is waterproof, snowproof, dropproof, shockproof and dustproof with front/back scratch resistant clear screen protector. Designed to meet/exceed military standards and tested up to 6.6ft/2m drops.100% access to Fingerprint ID, Audio/USB-C ports, silent switch and volume/power buttons. NOTE: Smartphone with extra screen protector will lose sensitive touch. Notes: Please make sure the system of your phone is updated once and then perform fingerprint recognition again with our phone case on, which is key to a successful fingerprint unlock.For a better experience, remove any pre-installed screen protector on your phone before installation.The size of the charging port opening is not big enough (only 12.8mm*6.45mm) for other replacement charger. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
Reviewed in the United States on December 23, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works well on my A53 5G
reviews.reviewText: I bought 2 of these, one for me and one for my girlfriend since we upgraded phones. It fit nicely and snug and I attached the lanyard that comes with it. It seems to do what it's meant to do, I ran it through the sink to see if water got in it and it worked. I don't go swimming nor shower with it, but I do go off-roading and the elements seem to get the phone wet or dirty. This would help keep the phone looking new and add an additional layer of waterproof. Keep in mind that the A53 5G is already water resistant but having an extra layer of security gives me more piece of mind. I recommend this case if you are in areas were your phone could end up getting wet or dirty like outdoors.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Had to destroy it to get it off
reviews.reviewText: The cover seemed very sturdy, seemed like it was probably very waterproof as advertised. But I needed to remove it to listen to audio on my doorbell camera footage, as sound was rather muffled with the cover on. It was so impossible to remove I had to end up tearing it apart and destroying it just to get it off.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Phone would not work when it was installed in this case
reviews.reviewText: Bought this for a new phone, liked the fact that it had a screen protector and was waterproof.1st thing the case was difficult to install phone in due to the waterproof fit (almost gave up trying to install thought I might break something).When phone was in case it did not receive text messages or phone calls. Used for 2 days----thought something is off---no calls--no texts for 2 days.Could not get codes for verification to online accounts (Amazon included). What is different from the last 2 weeks of using this new phone?----the case !Removed phone from case and the "Flood Gates" opened-- 32 text messages and several missed calls immediately came through.Why?What caused the phone to not work while it was in this case?A mystery without any Clues.Returned for a refund
